# History: tooling-precommit-check-convention-to-invariant

This file preserves previous versions of the skill before amendments.

## v1.1.0 (2026-06-23)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus — issue #1550, R1 re-plan after a plan
reviewer graded v1.0.0 a B and NOGO'd it for parser brittleness.

**Verification:** unverified — still a PLAN (R1 re-plan), not executed code. The
R1 redesign was DESIGNED this session but the check script, its hook, and its
unit tests were NOT written or run; the "real PYSEC-2025-183 passes" claim
remains read-not-run (the workflow now mandates executing it, but execution has
not happened).

### What changed
- **Replaced the per-ID contiguous-comment-block walk (`_ledger_block_for`) with
  a whole-contiguous-comment-REGION parse.** v1.0.0 walked the comment paragraph
  around each vuln ID and stopped at any bare `#` (blank-comment) line. The R1
  parser instead collects the MAXIMAL run of comment lines ending directly above
  the `pip-audit = "..."` line — INCLUDING bare `#` separator lines (a bare `#`
  must NOT terminate the region) — then per suppressed ID requires (a) the ID
  appears in the region AND (b) a `Re-review:` line appears at-or-after the ID's
  first mention. Strictly more robust; survives blank-comment separators.
- **Added a fail-CLOSED guard for an unparseable task value.** The single-line
  regex `^\s*pip-audit\s*=\s*"([^"]*)"\s*$` cannot read a triple-quoted
  multi-line TOML string. The guard cross-checks the RAW file text for
  `--ignore-vuln`; if the raw count exceeds the parsed count (or no single-line
  task matched but raw text has `--ignore-vuln`), it emits a `<parser>` finding
  so the check FAILS LOUDLY rather than silently passing zero suppressions on a
  security ledger (cf. `gha-security-scanning-supply-chain` "no silent caps").
- **Added adversarial unit tests** mirroring the sibling test's
  `sys.path.insert(0, scripts_dir)` bootstrap: bare-`#`-separator-in-region must
  PASS (the exact v1.0.0 false-positive), multi-line/triple-quoted task must FAIL
  closed, and two IDs where only one is documented flags exactly the undocumented
  one. The "real ledger passes" assertion now requires ACTUALLY running the check
  and asserting `exit == 0`, not a file read.
- Converted the three v1.0.0 "(ASSUMPTION — unverified)" Failed Attempts rows into
  resolved rows describing the NOGO and its R1 fix; added new tags
  (`parse-whole-comment-region`, `fail-closed-on-unparseable`,
  `kiss-beats-cleverness`, `adversarial-tests`); added an R1-redesign Overview
  note and a second "Verified On" row. Bumped version 1.0.0 -> 1.1.0.

### Why
A plan reviewer NOGO'd v1.0.0's `_ledger_block_for` per-ID block walk (graded B)
because it stops at any bare `#` line: a LEGAL ledger layout where a bare `#`
separates the header from a vuln's paragraph would truncate the region and
FALSE-POSITIVE on a valid ledger. The converging fix removed the clever per-item
logic in favor of a coarser whole-region invariant — simpler AND more robust at
once (KISS beat cleverness). The single-line regex also risked a silent
FALSE-NEGATIVE on a multi-line task, the worst outcome for a security gate, so it
gained a fail-closed raw-text backstop. These are the durable learnings of the R1
re-plan.

